  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Chef",
  "description": "<p>As an Assistant Chef at Ti10 Services Pte Ltd, you will play a crucial role in supporting the kitchen operations and delivering  exceptional dining experiences. Working closely with the Head Chef, you  will be responsible for executing tasks across food preparation,  cooking, and kitchen management. This full-time position is based in the  Central Region, offering you the opportunity to be part of a dynamic  hospitality team.</p><p><strong>What you'll be doing</strong></p><ul><li>Assist with the preparation of high-quality, creative dishes as per the menu specifications</li><li>Ensure  the kitchen operates efficiently by supporting with tasks such as stock  management, equipment maintenance, and cleaning procedures</li><li>Maintain the highest standards of food safety and hygiene in the kitchen</li><li>Contribute to the development and implementation of new menu items</li><li>Collaborate with the culinary team to deliver a seamless dining experience for customers</li><li>Support the Head Chef in managing and supervising kitchen staff as required</li><li>Preferably able to cook Chinese cuisine</li></ul><p><strong>What we're looking for</strong></p><ul><li>Previous experience as an Assistant Chef or Commis Chef in a reputable hospitality establishment</li><li>Comprehensive knowledge of food preparation techniques, kitchen operations, and food safety regulations</li><li>Ability to work well under pressure and as part of a team</li><li>Strong attention to detail and commitment to maintaining high standards</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Flexibility to work in a fast-paced environment, including evenings, weekends, and public holidays</li><li>Possess Food Safety Course Level 1</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>AWS</li><li>Performance Bonus</li><li>Medical and Dental Coverage</li><li>Additional Staff benefits up to $1150 a year</li><li>5 days work week</li></ul>",
